  "DECISIVE": "POSITIVE (architecture rescues leaky recognition): a per-hop-gated relay tolerates per-hop false-positive up to q_n~0.30 while keeping normal-tissue kill <=1% -- ~15.0x the per-cell worst-donor bar (0.02). Below the percolation threshold (c*q_n<0.5) a false-positive normal cell starts a wave that DIES OUT (sub-critical, bounded rind) instead of cascading, while the tumour (c*q_t=0.77>0.5) clears from 3% seeds. A 7% slice of (q_t,q_n) space is both cleared (>90%) and spared (<1%). 3D SENSITIVITY (realistic, conservative): 3D tissue percolates easier (p_c~0.25), so the 3D safe q_n ceiling is 0.17 (~8.6x the per-cell bar) -- still well above 0.02. => propagation can convert a recognition signal TOO LEAKY for R5's per-cell gate into a safe therapy -- IF coupling is engineered and gating re-checked per hop. The recognition bottleneck is RELAXED, not removed (still need q_n below the percolation threshold; mapping to a molecular gate + coupling efficiency is the wet-lab residual).",
  "CEILING": "ABSTRACTION (2D site-bond percolation): q_t/q_n/c are swept PARAMETERS not measured molecular fidelities; mapping them to a real gate (RUNG-11 neoantigen / synNotch) + engineered coupling is the wet-lab residual. No 3D/diffusion/immune/graded-signal. The robust parameter-free claim is the RELATIONSHIP: relay leak is sub-critical-BOUNDED vs per-cell leak LINEAR -> threshold-protected safety margin."
